Well, I guess your thoughts of revenge would disappear, your anger would go away,

233
00:23:56,740 --> 00:24:00,090
and so would any hatred and resentment,

234
00:24:00,090 --> 00:24:04,600
I suppose you'd live peacefully, with a kind and loving heart.

235
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,030
Why?

236
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:14,140
You're the one who needs to have amnesia. You're the one who needs to lose her memory, seriously.

237
00:24:14,140 --> 00:24:16,190
What did you say?

238
00:24:16,190 --> 00:24:20,420
It'd be nice to deposit memories into a bank.

239
00:24:20,420 --> 00:24:24,230
If my memories were deposited into a savings account,

240
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:29,650
then it'd be nice to just be able to withdraw and use them whenever I needed.

241
00:24:41,490 --> 00:24:45,920
I have a long way to go if I want to follow in your footsteps, Father-in-law.

242
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:51,940
I couldn't foresee a second ahead of time like a fool so I believed and thought you were my side.

243
00:24:51,940 --> 00:24:58,260
I felt guilty and sorry without knowing you sit there and think only about getting rid of me everyday.

244
00:24:58,260 --> 00:25:04,980
I don't know about anyone else, but I suppose you'd be the one to know about the anxiety I'm feeling that's driving me crazy...

245
00:25:08,870 --> 00:25:13,150
I was foolish. I guess I've always been a bit foolish.

246
00:25:13,150 --> 00:25:19,620
I understand. Yes, I get it now, Father-in-law. Now that I've completely grasped your true intention,

247
00:25:20,690 --> 00:25:24,150
it's war from now on, Father-in-law.

248
00:25:25,580 --> 00:25:30,060
If you wave a knife at me, then I'll shoot you with a gun.

249
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:35,270
But rather than it hitting you, I think it'll be your son, who's cluelessly running wild, ending up taking the bullet—

250
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:37,950
That's my worry.

251
00:25:37,950 --> 00:25:43,600
Don't worry. Because my son can just shoot you first.

252
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:49,780
Because, even if I forgive you, that guy will never be able to forgive you.

253
00:25:49,780 --> 00:25:54,340
I may not be able to punish you, but that guy,

254
00:25:54,340 --> 00:25:59,030
when it comes to him, he can definitely punish you.

255
00:26:00,950 --> 00:26:04,830
You talk as if I'm the one who's done something wrong.

256
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:07,400
There is a difference.

257
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:12,600
The statute of limitations has expired for me. But it hasn't expired for you.

258
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:17,020
I may not have a lot of time left to live, but you

259
00:26:17,020 --> 00:26:19,790
have many years ahead of you.

260
00:26:27,940 --> 00:26:30,110
Let's have breakfast together, Brother-in-law.

261
00:26:30,110 --> 00:26:33,860
- I don't really feel like it today.
- Then come sit for a little while before you leave.

262
00:26:33,860 --> 00:26:35,690
Alright, I guess.

263
00:26:44,810 --> 00:26:48,290
Whenever it's possible, let's all make sure to have breakfast together.

264
00:26:48,290 --> 00:26:54,470
It's my wish, so everyone please stick to it. Choi Jin Eon, especially you.

265
00:26:54,470 --> 00:26:56,440
Okay.

266
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:59,100
Are you doing better now?

267
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:00,400
Yes.

268
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:03,900
You see, because in Hae Gang's urn—Hae Gang isn't there.

269
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:06,500
Wh-What did you say?

270
00:27:06,500 --> 00:27:08,590
What isn't there?

271
00:27:08,590 --> 00:27:11,720
That's absurd! How can you say something so outrageous!

272
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:16,540
You mean there aren't any remains? Why is it? How can there not be any?

273
00:27:16,540 --> 00:27:22,190
I guess Brother-in-law would know that. Why is Hae Gang's urn empty?

274
00:27:25,940 --> 00:27:29,520
We never ended up finding her body.

275
00:27:31,310 --> 00:27:37,040
If you never found a body, but you confirmed her death,

276
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:41,030
I suppose there's a witness who's able to provide even more guarantee than Hae Gang's own body.

277
00:27:41,030 --> 00:27:44,370
Someone who was there with Hae Gang at the scene.

278
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:48,500
That's right. There's a witness who saw her fall into the dam.

279
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:51,530
And Father-in-law is the one who had the police report removed.

280
00:27:51,530 --> 00:27:53,960
<i>Since we can't let the whole world know about his daughter-in-law's suicide.</i>

281
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:57,910
I saw Hae Gang yesterday. A Hae Gang who's very much alive.

282
00:27:57,910 --> 00:28:01,290
What'd you say? She's alive?

283
00:28:01,290 --> 00:28:04,570
I'm sure you saw it wrong. Attorney Do is dead.

284
00:28:04,570 --> 00:28:07,650
Last time, you confused another person for Attorney Do too, remember?

285
00:28:07,650 --> 00:28:13,410
I suppose. Whether I'm confused,

286
00:28:13,410 --> 00:28:17,710
or whether Hae Gang is still alive. I'll check and find out.

287
00:28:17,710 --> 00:28:19,880
I thought—

288
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:26,550
Jin Eon. Jin Eon! Pull yourself together.

289
00:28:26,550 --> 00:28:31,160
<i>That's a disease. I'm telling you, it's not love, but a mental disease!</i>

290
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:34,640
All this really is, is that everyone looks like Do Hae Gang to you right now.

291
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:37,750
<i> I understand. The pain of losing your spouse.</i>

292
00:28:37,750 --> 00:28:42,120
You just don't want to admit it. You want to deny it.

293
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:47,260
But your the one who abandoned her. You were the one who asked Father to get rid of her.

294
00:28:47,260 --> 00:28:48,960
Omo, hey, hey!

295
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:51,670
Just stay still, please.

296
00:28:51,700 --> 00:28:55,500
Whether it was suicide or not, whether there are remains or not, however she died,

297
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:57,270
you're the one who made it end up like this.

298
00:28:57,270 --> 00:29:02,040
I'm saying this all happened because of you. Even if your wife came back alive,

299
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:06,030
with her personality, she would never forgive you.

300
00:29:06,030 --> 00:29:09,830
Only you miss her to death, Do Hae Gang hates you to death.

301
00:29:09,830 --> 00:29:14,410
<i>If she saw you, she'd want to take revenge on you.
How could you expect her to love you?</i>

302
00:29:14,410 --> 00:29:18,660
It's your sin. The original sin you started. It's the seed you sowed.

303
00:29:18,660 --> 00:29:23,840
<i>This is all a punishment. So quit obsessing over Do Hae Gang, and just receive your punishment, okay?</i>

304
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:28,040
When you planted hatred, how can you expect to sprout love?

305
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:42,810
What is this like salted vegetables? Head up and look at me.

306
00:29:47,090 --> 00:29:51,460
<i>Whenever you eat or you fight, you need to look at each other and do it.</i>

307
00:29:51,460 --> 00:29:54,800
<i>I'm telling to you guys to look at each other, instead of looking away from each other.</i>

308
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:57,000
<i>If you keep turning away from each other during tough times, </i>

309
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:00,800
<i>when the time comes that you want to look to each other, you won't be able to anymore. It'll be too late.</i>

310
00:30:01,660 --> 00:30:03,990
Did you get disappointed by Yong Gi?

311
00:30:05,010 --> 00:30:08,310
<i>It's a given for family to disappoint each other.</i>

312
00:30:08,310 --> 00:30:13,330
One minute it's disappointment, the next it's hope, then desire.

313
00:30:13,330 --> 00:30:15,330
That's family.

314
00:30:16,220 --> 00:30:22,010
Don't hold a grudge but believe each other and speak out honestly when you fight.

315
00:30:22,010 --> 00:30:27,760
If you hold a grudge and not speak out, you will really get narrow-minded.

316
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:30,320
People's hearts, too.

317
00:30:31,840 --> 00:30:36,310
She's not family, yet.

318
00:30:39,140 --> 00:30:43,590
Don't trap Yong Gi by calling her family, Father.

319
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:50,560
You were always honest.

320
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:55,360
You always looked directly into my eyes and told me honestly.

321
00:30:58,970 --> 00:31:01,410
The one who can't do it is me.

322
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:09,690
<i>I'm in the middle of thinking things through and agonizing over them.</i>

323
00:31:11,580 --> 00:31:15,710
Just give me a little more time. Then,

324
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:21,680
I will look at your eyes and honestly fight with you.

325
00:31:32,020 --> 00:31:36,730
Mom. Am I getting a shot today?

326
00:31:36,730 --> 00:31:39,220
Today, just an exam.

327
00:31:41,170 --> 00:31:43,620
Should we play that?

328
00:31:48,060 --> 00:31:49,380
Ms. Zhang Ming!

329
00:31:49,380 --> 00:31:50,870
Oh yes, I'm right here, Zhang Ming.

330
00:31:50,870 --> 00:31:54,440
- Please come in.
- Yes.

331
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:55,950
Let's go in, Woo Joo.

332
00:31:55,950 --> 00:31:58,080
This way, please.

333
00:32:01,430 --> 00:32:07,380
Come on, let's sit you down. Thank you.

334
00:32:08,460 --> 00:32:09,890
Aren't you going to greet the doctor?

335
00:32:09,890 --> 00:32:12,170
Ni hao! ("Hello!" in Chinese)

336
00:32:12,170 --> 00:32:15,380
Welcome, Dokgo Woo Joo.

337
00:32:17,870 --> 00:32:22,010
I already told you her name isn't Dokgo Woo Joo,
so why do you keep—

338
00:32:24,100 --> 00:32:26,560
I'll sit down.

339
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:32,420
Why don't you start by telling me her symptoms—in Korean.

340
00:32:32,420 --> 00:32:34,510
Pardon?

341
00:32:34,510 --> 00:32:36,450
Ah, that's—

342
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:40,820
My child was falling down all the time, so I took her to the local hospital— <i>(spoken in dialect)</i>

343
00:32:40,820 --> 00:32:42,420
- <i> Next patient.</i>
- Excuse me?

344
00:32:42,420 --> 00:32:46,820
What are you doing? See these people out, and bring in the next patients.

345
00:32:46,820 --> 00:32:50,020
The relationship between the doctor and the patient starts with respect.

346
00:32:50,020 --> 00:32:53,720
If the basics are wrong, rarities can't be cured.

347
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:56,370
Korean—

348
00:32:57,220 --> 00:32:58,680
I can just speak Korean, then.

349
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:04,400
Okay, then. Please tell me Woo Joo's symptoms.

350
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:09,750
She falls down easily and has anemia.

351
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:13,620
She was being treated for leukemia but it didn't seem right.

352
00:33:13,620 --> 00:33:16,730
Strange cells were seen in her bone marrow.

353
00:33:16,730 --> 00:33:19,180
Looked like it may be Gaucher's disease.

354
00:33:20,610 --> 00:33:25,110
Since you are the expert in this field, I came to Korea because of you.

355
00:33:25,110 --> 00:33:28,270
Let's have a basic examination and an enzyme analysis right away.

356
00:33:28,270 --> 00:33:30,510
It's difficult to determine by bone marrow tests alone.

357
00:33:30,510 --> 00:33:33,300
Gaucher cells are not always found in the bone marrow.

358
00:33:33,300 --> 00:33:38,470
Since there are many similar cells, though it may be more costly, you must get an enzyme analysis.

359
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:51,920
<i>Hong Se Hee!</i>

360
00:34:23,510 --> 00:34:26,800
You're so pretty. What's your name?

361
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:27,740
Zhang Ling.

362
00:34:27,740 --> 00:34:31,750
Zhang Ling? You must have come from China, is that right?

363
00:34:40,410 --> 00:34:45,620
What's the matter? Is there something on my face?

364
00:34:49,790 --> 00:34:51,810
<i>Dokgo Yong Gi.</i>

365
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:55,740
I swear, really!

366
00:35:01,650 --> 00:35:03,480
Passport.

367
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:08,200
Instead, please pay me back 57,520 won.

368
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:10,360
Are you not going to pay me?

369
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:12,320
I'm going to find some work today, okay?

370
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:15,820
I'm planning to do whatever work comes my way as soon as I can, without being picky whatsoever, so

371
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:18,280
please just give me a few days.

372
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:22,240
I'll give you three days. In three days,

373
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:24,610
by 2:47pm, please pay me back by then.

374
00:35:25,910 --> 00:35:27,630
Fine.

375
00:35:54,910 --> 00:35:59,580
Your name is Dokgo Yong Gi?

376
00:35:59,580 --> 00:36:01,090
Pardon?

377
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:06,010
No, it's not! The doctor got it wrong.

378
00:36:06,750 --> 00:36:11,230
My name is Zhang Ming! Zhang Ming.

379
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:19,650
But—why are you staring at me like that?

380
00:36:19,650 --> 00:36:22,490
I've never seen you before.

381
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:45,200
<i>Female Plaintiff in Lawsuit for Damages from Medication Side Effects, Jumps Off Court Building</i>

382
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:49,370
<i>That woman is on a different level from Yong Gi Unni.</i>

383
00:36:49,370 --> 00:36:53,030
<i>She's cold-hearted and cruel.</i>

384
00:36:56,700 --> 00:37:02,500
<i>Pharmaceutical Chemist Loses Patent Infringement Lawsuit, Murders Opposing Attorney's Daughter in Retaliation</i>

385
00:37:02,510 --> 00:37:04,680
<i>Her daughter died.</i>

386
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:06,930
<i> Because of his wife.</i>

